00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:22,960
你们上过我的一些课程
You've done some of my other courses.

343
00:35:23,120 --> 00:35:27,760
有些人没上过 晚上好 你们可以叫我"大厨"
Those of you that don't, buonasera, and you can call me "Chef."

344
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:30,520
我们将会分组完成课程…
We'll be working in pairs throughout the course...

345
00:35:30,680 --> 00:35:35,200
…所以今天我想先做的一件事情 就是把你们分好组
...so one of the first things I want to do today is to pair you all up.

346
00:35:35,680 --> 00:35:38,120
好吗？别害羞 挑个同伴
All right? Don't be shy. Grab a partner.

347
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:40,360
我看见你们当中已经有人组好了队
I see some of you have come in twos already.

348
00:35:40,520 --> 00:35:42,960
还有些人以前一起合作过
Others have worked together before.

349
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:45,240
好 现在还剩下谁？
Okay. Now who's left?

350
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:48,520
打扰一下 天啊 抱歉
Excuse me. God. I'm sorry.

351
00:35:48,720 --> 00:35:50,440
很抱歉我来晚了
I'm so sorry I'm late.

352
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:52,480
不知为什么道路封闭了…
The roads were closed for some reason...

353
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:58,080
而且注册的那个混蛋 花了很长时间才处理完我的申请
...plus this jerk in registration took an age processing my application.

354
00:35:58,240 --> 00:35:59,480
我是不是来得太晚了？
Am I too late?

355
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:02,720
不 不 不 一点都不 你叫什么？
No. No, no. Not at all. What is your name?

356
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:05,160
- 梅拉尼  - 我们正在分组
- Melanie. - We were just pairing people off.

357
00:36:05,320 --> 00:36:08,040
你为什么不和…
Why don't we put you with....

358
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:10,040
- 你叫什么？- 乔治
- What is your name? - George.

359
00:36:10,240 --> 00:36:12,960
梅拉尼和乔治一组 还有 爱丽丝 你和…
Melanie with George. And, Alice, you're with....

360
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:14,800
汤尼
Tony.

361
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:16,520
你好吗 汤尼？
How you doing, Tony?

362
00:36:16,720 --> 00:36:18,360
- 抱歉  - 好的
- Sorry. - All right.

363
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:22,400
现在 在练习课上 你们自由发挥
Now, in exercise class, you warm up with stretches.

364
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:25,280
我们将会来一杯巴巴瑞斯 可暖暖身子…
We're gonna warm up with a glass of Barbaresco...

365
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:29,360
…来自意大利西北部山麓地域的美酒…
...a beautiful wine from the piedmont region in northwestern Italy...

366
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:32,160
- …由内比奥罗的葡萄酿制而成   - 嗨 乔治
- ...made from the Nebbiolo grape. - Hi. George.

367
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:35,160
尝一下
Take a sip.

368
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:41,240
嗯 嗯
Mm. Mm.

369
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:44,600
再来点音乐
And some music.

370
00:36:47,040 --> 00:36:53,200
因为烹饪就是一项感官运动 对吧？嗅觉 视觉 还有听觉
Because cooking is all the senses, right? The nose, the eyes, the palate and the ears.

371
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:55,600
今晚 我们先从最基础的开始学起
And tonight, we're gonna start at the beginning.

372
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:58,760
博大精深的意大利厨艺的基础…
The cornerstone of so much of Italian cooking...

373
00:36:58,920 --> 00:37:01,800
…就是托斯卡纳经典的番茄沙司
...the classic tomato sauce from Toscana.

374
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:06,880
做准备工作 我们需要切番茄 那么开始切吧
And in preparation, we're gonna need chopped tomatoes, so let's get chopping.

375
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:12,800
慢慢来 一切就绪？看看这些漂亮的番茄 啊？
Take your time. Doing all right? Look at these beautiful tomatoes, huh?

376
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:15,880
啊 音乐 是不是很美妙？
Ah, the music. Is this beautiful?

377
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:23,000
天啊 有些人真的很厉害
God, some of them are really good.

378
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:25,680
你第一次做饭？
Is this your first time?

379
00:37:25,840 --> 00:37:28,280
- 是的  - 哦 我也是
- Yeah. - Yeah, mine too.

380
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:32,720
我在册子上看到该课程建立了竞争机制
I read in the brochure that the course builds to a competition.

381
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:37,280
看到了 由当地餐馆评论家来评判
I saw that. To be judged by a local restaurant critic.

382
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:41,320
是的 我想我们就不用报以希望了 呵呵
Yeah. I don't think we should get our hopes up. Heh, heh.

383
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:43,800
哦 我们还有10周的时间呢
Well, we still have 10 weeks.

384
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:47,200
- 对 没错  - 而且我们现在还没有切到手
- Well, that's true. - And we haven't cut our fingers off yet.

385
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:51,640
说得没错
That's a good attitude.

386
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:59,280
我们俩谁用错刀子了？我吗？
Which one of us is using the wrong knife? Am I using the wrong knife?

387
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:01,680
对 你应该用那个
Yeah. You're using that.

388
00:38:02,920 --> 00:38:05,080
我旁边那个大妈自己带着刀子来的
The woman next to me brought her own knife.

389
00:38:06,080 --> 00:38:08,560
- 是吗？- 倍感威胁啊
- Really? - Very intimidating.

390
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:14,120
那么下周见
So I'll see you next week.

391
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:16,600
好 耶 下周见
Great. Yeah. See you next week.

392
00:38:43,680 --> 00:38:46,360
- 乔治·洛里根？- 对
- George Lonegan? - Yeah.

393
00:38:46,520 --> 00:38:47,560
不想打扰你的
I hate to bother you.

394
00:38:47,760 --> 00:38:50,200
我是安德鲁先生的邻居
I'm Mr. Andreou's neighbor.

395
00:38:51,120 --> 00:38:54,040
希腊人 50来岁 他的妻子死了
The Greek guy, mid-fifties, who lost his wife.

396
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:57,400
我知道你最近为他做过通灵
I believe you recently did a reading for him.

397
00:38:57,560 --> 00:38:59,200
- 我正想阻止你  - 坎迪斯
- I'm just gonna stop you. - Candace.

398
00:38:59,360 --> 00:39:02,640
好的 坎迪斯 我再也不通灵了
Okay, Candace, I don't do readings anymore.

399
00:39:03,120 --> 00:39:05,200
你上周为安德鲁先生做了一次
You did one last week for Mr. Andreou.

400
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:08,080
他是我哥哥的朋友 那次是特例
He's an associate of my brother's. It was a one-time thing.

401
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:10,760
拜托 我向你保证 我不会告诉别人的
please, I give you my word. I won't tell anyone.

402
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:14,600
- 抱歉   - 听着 听着 听着 我带钱过来了
- I'm sorry. - Listen, listen, listen. I brought money.

403
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:16,840
- 我不要你的钱   - 要什么都可以
- I don't want your money. - Everything I have.

404
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:19,840
我失去了我的孩子
I lost my child.

405
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:23,240
我唯一的孩子 她还是个婴儿
My only child. Just a baby.

406
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:24,960
我只想跟她说说话
I just wanna talk to her.

407
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:26,880
求你了 我想和我的孩子说话
please, I wanna talk to my baby.

408
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:29,640
我帮不了你 我再也不做了！
I can't help you. I don't do that anymore!

409
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:33,200
- 拜托！  - 洛里根先生！我有钱！
- please! - Mr. Lonegan! I got money!

410
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:37,760
洛里根先生 求求你
Mr. Lonegan. please.

411
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:45,160
我想和我的孩子说话
I wanna talk to my baby.

412
00:39:46,040 --> 00:39:49,480
上啊 姑娘们！很好！踢！
Go, girls! There you go! Kick it!

413
00:39:49,640 --> 00:39:52,000
又有个人来找我通灵
So another person came to see me for a reading.

414
00:39:53,240 --> 00:39:56,000
都是你朋友安德鲁干的好事
Thanks to your friend Mr. Andreou.

415
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:57,920
- 什么？- 没错
- What? - Yeah.

416
00:39:58,080 --> 00:40:00,800
我告诉过那个希腊佬要守口如瓶
Told that Greek jerk to keep his big mouth shut.

417
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:03,600
上啊 姑娘们！踢回去！踢回去呀！
Go, girls! Kick it back! You gotta kick it back!

418
00:40:03,800 --> 00:40:06,160
很显然他没有
Well, obviously he didn't.

419
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:09,680
我会跟他说的 确保不会再发生这种事
I'll talk with him, make sure nothing like that ever happens again.

420
00:40:09,840 --> 00:40:11,320
好
Okay.

421
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:14,480
后来呢？
And?

422
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:17,960
- 后来什么？- 你帮她了吗？
- And what? - Did you do it?

423
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:20,080
- 什么？  - 通灵？
- What? - The reading.

424
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:23,160
- 你帮她通灵了吗？  - 你还是不明白 是吧？
- Did you do the reading? - You still don't get it, do you?

425
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:26,160
你以为就因为我能靠这个挣钱…
You think just because I can make money doing this...

426
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:29,080
…就因为我会 我就应该做？
...just because I can that I should do it.

427
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:30,960
是啊 我真这么想
Yeah. Yeah, I do.

428
00:40:31,120 --> 00:40:34,680
我还觉得你有这个义务 因为你有天分
I also think you have a duty to do it because you have a gift.

429
00:40:34,840 --> 00:40:37,320
这不是天分 比利 是诅咒
It's not a gift, Billy. It's a curse.

430
00:40:38,240 --> 00:40:42,880
你完全不懂 它毁掉了我所有能过正常生活的机会
You have no idea. It ruins any chance I have at a normal life.

431
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:44,080
就像个怪物
Feel like a freak.

432
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:47,920
怪物？
Freak?

433
00:40:48,120 --> 00:40:50,080
不管像不像怪物 乔治 这就是你
Freak or not, Georgie, it's who you are.

434
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:53,320
这就是你 你不能永远逃避下去
It's what you are, you know. You can't run from that forever.

435
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:15,080
为了让他的思绪离开那哀伤的话题…
To divert his thoughts from this melancholy subject...

436
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:19,800
…我告诉迈卡赫先生 我需要他帮我做一杯潘趣酒…
...I informed Mr. Micawher that I relied on him for a bowl of punch...

437
00:41:19,960 --> 00:41:22,040
…并带他找到柠檬
...and led him to the lemons

438
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:27,720
他近来那消沉的意气 虽说不上是绝望 但也在刹那间消逝了
His recent despondency, not to say despair, was gone in a moment.

439
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:30,760
我从没见过一个如此自得其乐的人…
I never saw a man so thoroughly enjoy himself...

440
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:36,400
煮沸的朗姆酒的香气里…
...amid the fragrance of lemon peel and sugar, and the smell of burning rum...

441
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:39,360
…他在搅拌 调酒和品尝的时候…
...as he stirred and mixed and tasted...

442
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:42,200
…就仿佛他在做的 不是潘趣酒…
...and looked as if he were making, instead of punch...

443
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:47,680
…而是一份将永传于后世的家族财富
...a fortune for his family to last for all posterity.

444
00:41:59,360 --> 00:42:02,040
死亡不是终点 仅仅是个开始
Death is not final. It is merely the beginning.

445
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:07,200
通往映射出我们在这世所为的后世
Gateway to an afterlife that reflects our conduct here on earth.

446
00:42:08,680 --> 00:42:11,200
上帝 以其无上的慷慨 创造了天堂…
God, in his infinite generosity, has created heaven...

447
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:12,920
…如今杰森便在那里…
...which is where Jason is now...

448
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:17,680
…看着我们 身旁站满了天使和圣徒
...surrounded by all the angels and saints, looking down at us.

449
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:24,160
我们将杰森的遗体归为尘土 他的灵魂将永栖主怀
And so we commit Jason's body to dust, his soul already in God's care.

450
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:36,560
杰森的骨灰会从后门送出去…
Jason's ashes will be available at the back...

451
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:40,840
…但你不介意的话 我希望你从前门出去
...but if you wouldn't mind, I'd like you to leave through the front door.

452
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:45,440
早上好
Morning.

453
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:48,640
请进
please come in.

454
00:42:49,560 --> 00:42:50,760
谢谢
Thank you.

455
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:57,720
早上好
Morning.

456
00:44:01,720 --> 00:44:03,200
晚安 贾斯
Good night, Jase.

457
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:07,360
不会一直这样 只是短期这样安排
It won't be for long. It's a short-term placement.

458
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:09,160
直到你妈妈好起来
Just until your mum feels better.

459
00:44:09,360 --> 00:44:13,480
我们在考虑的那对夫妇很有经验 而且就住你家附近
The couple we have in mind have a lot of experience and live close to where you live.

460
00:44:13,640 --> 00:44:16,360
当然你也就不用转学了
Of course you'll stay at the same school.

461
00:44:27,760 --> 00:44:30,480
我不想跟别人走
I don't wanna go with anyone else.

462
00:44:30,880 --> 00:44:32,600
我想和你在一起
I wanna stay with you.

463
00:44:33,160 --> 00:44:34,800
你要去哪里？
Where are you going?

464
00:44:36,520 --> 00:44:39,640
让我们单独呆一会 好吗？
Just give us a minute, will you?

465
00:44:51,480 --> 00:44:56,160
听着 我需要一点时间整理自己
Look, I need a little time to sort myself out.

466
00:44:57,480 --> 00:45:01,440
但我保证 我不会逃跑
But I'm not running away, I promise.

467
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:08,040
我现在可以和你在一起 我也很想这样
I could stay with you now, and I want that so much.

468
00:45:08,200 --> 00:45:12,240
但我有可能做不到 因为我还不够强大
But chances are I wouldn't make it, because I'm not strong enough.

469
00:45:21,520 --> 00:45:24,120
我不奢望你能理解
I don't expect you to understand.

470
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:31,400
我知道我现在丢下你…
And I know for me to leave you now...

471
00:45:31,600 --> 00:45:34,800
…肯定会觉得做了世上最坏的事情
...it must feel like the worst thing in the world.

472
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:42,080
但我向你保证不会让你失望 好吗？
But I promise you I'm not gonna let you down, okay?

473
00:45:44,120 --> 00:45:45,840
我向你保证
I promise you.

474
00:45:51,280 --> 00:45:53,160
真的对不起
I'm so sorry.

475
00:45:53,320 --> 00:45:55,320
我爱你 来
I love you. Come here.

476
00:46:29,720 --> 00:46:31,200
过来
Come here.

477
00:46:35,080 --> 00:46:36,560
要乖乖的
Be a good boy.

478
00:46:50,120 --> 00:46:52,040
走吧
Come on.

479
00:47:08,720 --> 00:47:13,280
通观战后的法国历史 只有两个像样的政治家
Summing up France's postwar history, only two statesmen counted:

480
00:47:13,440 --> 00:47:15,080
戴高乐和他
De Gaulle and him.

481
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:20,120
戴高乐所有的事情都被写过了 而密特朗希望能由我来完成
On de Gaulle, everything's been written. On Mitterrand, I want to finish the job.

482
00:47:20,280 --> 00:47:22,000
他身上有很多引人注目的元素
There are fascinating elements.

483
00:47:22,160 --> 00:47:24,400
废除死刑 加入欧盟
The abolition of the death penalty, the European Union.

484
00:47:24,560 --> 00:47:26,920
生于右翼分子家庭 却领导着左翼党派
Coming from a right-wing family, he seduced the left.

485
00:47:27,080 --> 00:47:29,080
更重要的是 使他们信奉自由主义
And what's more, converted it to liberalism.

486
00:47:29,240 --> 00:47:31,560
了不起！简直是场革命 对不对？
Amazing! It was a revolution, right?

487
00:47:31,760 --> 00:47:35,720
再加上他从未被发现的性格上的阴暗面
plus the darker sides of his character that have never been explored.

488
00:47:35,920 --> 00:47:39,800
他已经死了10年 时机正好 我们可以深入挖掘
He's been dead for 10 years. The timing is right, we can dig deeper.

489
00:47:39,960 --> 00:47:41,400
我想潜入他的过去
I want to dig into his past.

490
00:47:41,600 --> 00:47:44,560
维希 ELF石油公司的丑闻… 他扮演着什么角色？
Vichy, the Elf scandal.... What part did he play?

491
00:47:44,720 --> 00:47:46,640
台湾护卫舰事件 巴芃丑闻…
The Taiwan frigates, the papon scandal...

492
00:47:46,840 --> 00:47:48,240
…玛莎琳 玛格丽特·杜拉斯
...Mazarine, Marguerite Duras.

493
00:47:48,400 --> 00:47:51,560
这些从没有被真正报道过 它们都被埋没了
These stories were never really addressed. They've all been buried.

494
00:47:51,720 --> 00:47:54,120
我要找出那些知情者 那些未曾开口的人
I'm going to tell who knew, who didn't talk.

495
00:47:54,280 --> 00:47:57,080
这会不会给我们带来太多争议？
Isn't that going to bring us too much controversy?

496
00:47:57,240 --> 00:47:58,880
我不这么认为
I don't think so.

497
00:47:59,400 --> 00:48:01,560
我想要的是一本人人都能看的书
What I want is a book that can be read by all.

498
00:48:01,720 --> 00:48:04,520
密特朗不仅仅是个政治家
Mitterrand was not just a politician.

499
00:48:05,120 --> 00:48:07,080
密特朗是一尊圣像
Mitterrand was an icon.

500
00:48:07,280 --> 00:48:09,160
他是我们的叔叔 （法国人对前总统密特朗的昵称！）
He's "Tonton," our uncle!

501
