A 360 perspective?

853
01:16:51,320 --> 01:16:54,040
感觉不到时间和物体的移动？
No sense of linear time or motion?

854
01:16:54,200 --> 01:16:55,440
对
Yes.

855
01:16:55,640 --> 01:16:57,360
但什么都知道 什么都有感觉？
But all-knowing, all-sensing?

856
01:16:57,520 --> 01:16:58,720
正是这样
Exactly.

857
01:16:58,920 --> 01:17:01,080
- 来杯茶吗？  - 谢谢
- Would you care for some tea? - Thank you.

858
01:17:01,280 --> 01:17:05,280
你知道 作为一名科学家和无神论者…
You know, as a scientist and atheist...

859
01:17:05,480 --> 01:17:08,240
…我打心里对那些事是抗拒的
...my mind was closed to such things.

860
01:17:08,400 --> 01:17:12,040
噢 当然 死后 接近死亡的经历
Oh, absolutely. Afterlife, near-death experiences.

861
01:17:12,200 --> 01:17:15,160
和每个人一样 我想人们应该会看到亮光…
Like everyone else, I thought people saw bright lights...

862
01:17:15,320 --> 01:17:17,200
…伊甸园那样的花园什么的…
...Eden-like gardens and so forth...

863
01:17:17,400 --> 01:17:21,040
…因为这是传统文化决定的
...because they were culturally conditioned to do so.

864
01:17:21,240 --> 01:17:25,560
但在安养院待了25年后…
But after 25 years in a hospice...

865
01:17:25,720 --> 01:17:28,920
…工作对象是一些多数已经宣告死亡…
...working with people, many of whom were pronounced dead...

866
01:17:29,640 --> 01:17:32,280
…但奇迹般又活过来的人…
...but then miraculously survived...

867
01:17:32,480 --> 01:17:36,920
…他们所叙述的经历是那么令人心惊地相似…
...the account of what they actually experienced were so strikingly similar...

868
01:17:37,080 --> 01:17:39,480
…不可能是巧合
...it couldn't just be coincidence.

869
01:17:41,560 --> 01:17:44,720
加之他们在经历这些的时候…
And add to that the fact that when they had these experiences...

870
01:17:44,880 --> 01:17:47,160
…完全属于无意识状态…
...they were almost all unconscious...

871
01:17:47,320 --> 01:17:52,880
…我的对手都同意那时候 大脑根本不能创造新的画面
...a state in which my enemies agree the brain cannot create fresh images.

872
01:17:55,160 --> 01:17:58,080
那你认为我是真的经历了某些东西？
So you think I really did experience something?

873
01:17:58,280 --> 01:17:59,560
噢 是的
Oh, yes.

874
01:18:01,200 --> 01:18:02,880
我想你经历过了死亡
I think you experienced death.

875
01:18:06,600 --> 01:18:08,560
都在这了
It's all here.

876
01:18:08,720 --> 01:18:12,920
如果你的征途跟我相似的话 恐怕不是件易事啊
I'm afraid if your journey is anything like mine, it won't be an easy one.

877
01:18:13,120 --> 01:18:14,960
这是个孤独的战场
It's a lonely field to plow.

878
01:18:15,120 --> 01:18:19,360
人们面对这个话题总是很不理智 甚至很敌意
people get quite irrational around this subject. Quite hostile, even.

879
01:18:19,520 --> 01:18:22,600
但这些证据是驳不倒的
But the evidence is irrefutable.

880
01:18:22,800 --> 01:18:24,480
我努力过了
I tried.

881
01:18:29,640 --> 01:18:31,920
你知道 也许像你这样的…
You know, perhaps someone like you...

882
01:18:33,280 --> 01:18:36,840
…在如此地位上 有如此影响力的人 能改变它
...in your position, and with your influence, can change that.

883
01:18:38,400 --> 01:18:39,880
我希望你可以
I hope you can.

884
01:18:40,360 --> 01:18:42,000
谢谢
Thank you.

885
01:18:44,000 --> 01:18:45,280
祝你好运
Good luck.

886
01:18:45,440 --> 01:18:47,120
我弄好以后会送还给你的
I'll send it back when I'm done.

887
01:19:20,360 --> 01:19:21,720
晚上好
Good evening.

888
01:19:21,880 --> 01:19:25,560
维旺迪(法国一家巨型媒体跨国集团)和电力巨擎VFM发表的联合声明
Following a joint statement by Vivendi and electricity giant VFM..

889
01:19:25,720 --> 01:19:28,280
…表示季利润超过预计…
...announcing higher than expected quarterly profits..

890
01:19:28,440 --> 01:19:33,800
…让我们想到法国金融危机的复苏 是不是要提前到来？
...we wonder if evoking France's economic downturn might be premature?

891
01:19:58,600 --> 01:20:00,360
来楼上一下
Like to see you upstairs.

892
01:20:08,400 --> 01:20:10,000
乔治 请坐
George, have a seat.

893
01:20:11,240 --> 01:20:14,400
你或许知道到了很多关于裁员的说法
You're probably aware there's been a lot of talk about cutbacks.

894
01:20:14,560 --> 01:20:15,600
是啊 我听说了
Yeah, I heard.

895
01:20:16,160 --> 01:20:19,680
嗯 不管怎样 看来诉讼案是工会摆平了…
Yeah. Anyway, seems the suits got together with the unions...

896
01:20:19,880 --> 01:20:24,000
…还提出了对考虑主动离职人员所能得的福利
...and came up with packages for anyone willing to consider voluntary redundancy.

897
01:20:24,480 --> 01:20:26,080
主动离职？
Voluntary redundancy?

898
01:20:26,240 --> 01:20:28,520
听着 如果你问我 这交易很好的呀
Look, if you ask me, the deal is pretty good.

899
01:20:28,760 --> 01:20:32,840
你会得到6个月的工资和2年的医保
You get six months' pay in your pocket with health insurance for two years.

900
01:20:33,000 --> 01:20:35,360
那 这些跟我有一毛钱关系吗？
So, what does this have to do with me?

901
01:20:41,520 --> 01:20:44,240
这真是个丑闻 你在那工作了3年吧？
It's a freaking scandal. You worked there three years?

902
01:20:44,440 --> 01:20:46,520
没翘过一天班 从没请过病假
You never missed a day, never called in sick.

903
01:20:46,680 --> 01:20:49,480
- 他说这不是针对个人的   - 那是英国标准
- He said it was nothing personal. - That's B.S.

904
01:20:49,680 --> 01:20:52,320
他是想保护那些有妻儿的人
He's trying to protect the guys who have wives and kids.

905
01:20:52,520 --> 01:20:55,120
- 你应该请一个律师  - 没钱请
- You should hire a lawyer. - I can't afford a lawyer.

906
01:20:55,320 --> 01:20:58,280
如果你需要帮忙找新工作 我可以帮你
If you need help getting another job, I'll help you with that.

907
01:20:58,480 --> 01:21:02,480
对吧？
I'll make calls. I'll make it happen. But you know what I think you should do, right?

908
01:21:02,640 --> 01:21:04,360
嗯 我知道
Yes, I do.

909
01:21:04,560 --> 01:21:08,600
你知道 网站还没关呢 等着你
You know, the website's still up. Waiting.

910
01:21:08,800 --> 01:21:11,360
这次会不一样的 乔治
It'd be different this time, George.

911
01:21:12,240 --> 01:21:15,880
我们可以加以控制 这样就不一样啦
We could control it. That's how it would be different.

912
01:21:16,040 --> 01:21:18,760
我们可以一天就接2次客 最多3次 小规模接待
We'd only do two clients a day, three, tops. Keep it small.

913
01:21:18,920 --> 01:21:21,800
不告诉他们你的电话号码 我们不告诉媒体
Don't give out your phone number. We won't talk to the media.

914
01:21:21,960 --> 01:21:24,440
上次我们可吸取教训了 对吧？
We learned our lesson with that the last time, right?

915
01:21:26,680 --> 01:21:29,120
考虑考虑呗 嗯？
Just think about it, all right?

916
01:21:36,720 --> 01:21:38,960
- 做得还好吧 乔治？- 是啊
- Doing all right, George? - Yeah.

917
01:21:39,120 --> 01:21:41,080
看着有点不开心哦
Look a little bummed out.

918
01:21:41,240 --> 01:21:43,360
听着 我要掺和一下帮你忙喽
Listen, I'll step in and partner with you.

919
01:21:43,560 --> 01:21:46,440
你跟我一起可以赢的啦 你知道不？
Me and you could win this thing, you know?

920
01:21:46,640 --> 01:21:48,040
- 干嘛不呢？- 嗯
- Why not? - Yeah.

921
01:21:48,760 --> 01:21:50,240
很好
Great.

922
01:21:50,480 --> 01:21:52,560
小心手指头
Watch your fingers there.

923
01:22:16,080 --> 01:22:18,160
- 你好？- 克莱尔？
- Hello? - Clare?

924
01:22:18,360 --> 01:22:20,840
我是丹尼斯 我想你得过来一下
Dennis. I think you should come over.

925
01:22:22,000 --> 01:22:24,400
嗯 当然可以 丹尼斯 我这就过来
Yeah, of course, Dennis. I'll come now.

926
01:22:27,000 --> 01:22:29,800
- 那里面有多少钱？- 200英镑
- How much was in here? - Two hundred pounds.

927
01:22:29,960 --> 01:22:32,880
我们打电话给学校了 他没去上学
We called the school. He never got there.

928
01:22:33,040 --> 01:22:34,840
现在这是怎么回事？
What happens now?

929
01:22:35,000 --> 01:22:37,240
嗯 我们不想牵扯到警方
Well, we don't want to involve the police.

930
01:22:37,400 --> 01:22:39,320
不 那是万不得己的时候才用的
No, that's really a last resort.

931
01:22:41,360 --> 01:22:43,320
如果他回来了 告诉我们好吗？
Will you let us know if he comes back?

932
01:22:44,000 --> 01:22:45,880
我们保持联系
We will be in touch.

933
01:22:47,360 --> 01:22:49,320
我送你们出去
I'll see you out.

934
01:23:00,800 --> 01:23:02,280
进来吧
There you go.

935
01:23:14,800 --> 01:23:17,840
恐怕我们的通灵者 休伊特先生 他很忙的
I'm afraid our sensitive, Mr. Hewitt, is very busy.

936
01:23:18,000 --> 01:23:20,720
他最快也得6个星期后才能见你
Earliest he could see you is six weeks' time.

937
01:23:20,880 --> 01:23:22,240
噢 天哪
Oh, dear.

938
01:23:22,400 --> 01:23:24,400
乔伊斯女士 我们的资深通灵者…
Mrs. Joyce, our senior sensitive...

939
01:23:24,600 --> 01:23:27,400
…今晚要做一个公众通灵 如果你有兴趣
...is doing a public reading tonight if you're interested.

940
01:23:27,560 --> 01:23:29,280
在演讲大厅
In the lecture hall.

941
01:23:29,640 --> 01:23:32,480
好的 我会碰碰运气的 谢谢
All right. I'll try my luck. Thank you.

942
01:23:34,000 --> 01:23:35,320
需要我帮忙吗？
Can I help you?

943
01:23:35,840 --> 01:23:37,280
噢 不用 谢谢了
Oh, no, thanks.

944
01:23:40,240 --> 01:23:42,800
我强烈的感觉到屋子里的气息
I'm getting a strong feeling over this side of the room.

945
01:23:44,320 --> 01:23:47,040
某个名字以字母"J"开头的人
Someone whose name starts with a "J."

946
01:23:49,720 --> 01:23:52,560
字母"J"对谁有特殊意义吗？有人吗？
Does the letter "J" mean anything to anyone? Anyone?

947
01:23:52,760 --> 01:23:54,440
有人吗？
Anyone?

948
01:23:54,960 --> 01:23:56,160
噢
Oh.

949
01:23:56,600 --> 01:23:58,320
别害羞嘛
Don't be shy.

950
01:23:59,240 --> 01:24:01,120
告诉我们你的名字 谢谢
Tell us your name, please.

951
01:24:02,200 --> 01:24:03,320
马克斯
Marcus.

952
01:24:04,040 --> 01:24:07,560
马克斯 马克斯 过来吧
Marcus. Marcus. Come on.

953
01:24:07,720 --> 01:24:09,760
上这儿来 好让我能看见你
Come up here where I can see you.

954
01:24:10,920 --> 01:24:12,280
好孩子
Good boy.

955
01:24:12,640 --> 01:24:17,280
这是个好孩子 马克斯 没事的 我不会伤害你的
There's a good boy, Marcus. That's right. I'm not going to hurt you.

956
01:24:18,560 --> 01:24:19,920
你真可爱
That's lovely.

957
01:24:20,360 --> 01:24:24,440
那 马克斯 你最近失去了某个人
Now, Marcus, you've lost someone recently.

958
01:24:25,400 --> 01:24:27,440
是跟你非常亲近的人吗？
Was it someone very close to you?

959
01:24:29,800 --> 01:24:33,120
他正在告诉我他的名字 是乔 或者杰克
He's telling me his name. It's Joe, or Jack.

960
01:24:33,840 --> 01:24:35,200
- 杰森  - 杰森 就这个
- Jason. - Jason, that's it.

961
01:24:35,360 --> 01:24:38,640
他跟你非常亲近 不是吗？他是你的亲人吗？
He was very close to you, wasn't he? Was he part of your family?

962
01:24:42,800 --> 01:24:44,360
是不是你爸爸？
Is it your dad?

963
01:24:46,680 --> 01:24:50,000
嗯 爸爸说别伤心…
Well, Daddy says please don't be sad...

964
01:24:50,160 --> 01:24:53,040
…要为他照顾好妈妈 你会的对吧？
...and to look after Mummy for him, will you?

965
01:24:53,200 --> 01:24:55,280
你会为他这样做的 对吧？
Will you do that for him?

966
01:24:56,000 --> 01:24:59,480
给马克斯一点掌声吧 女士们 先生们
Give Marcus a round of applause, ladies and gentlemen.

967
01:25:01,880 --> 01:25:03,800
真可爱的孩子
Lovely boy.

968
01:25:03,960 --> 01:25:06,440
当我进入恍惚状态…
And as I go into a trance...

969
01:25:07,280 --> 01:25:11,080
…我的灵魂引导者会通过我跟你讲话
...my spirit guide will speak to you through me.

970
01:25:14,520 --> 01:25:15,880
噢
Oh.

971
01:25:18,280 --> 01:25:21,160
是谁把我从灵魂世界召唤来的？
Who summons me from the spirit world?

972
01:25:22,520 --> 01:25:23,680
说出你的名字吧
Say your name.

973
01:25:24,200 --> 01:25:26,520
- 马克斯  - 马克斯
- Marcus. - Marcus.

974
01:25:26,680 --> 01:25:31,840
欢迎你 马克斯 我叫尧西
Welcome, Marcus. My name is Yoshi.

975
01:25:33,280 --> 01:25:36,560
我正在做的是调试麦克风
What I'm doing is I'm adjusting the level of the microphones.

976
01:25:36,720 --> 01:25:38,320
你在学校学物理吗？
Do you do physics at school?

977
01:25:38,480 --> 01:25:41,600
很好 那你知道声音有着不同的振动频率
Good. Then you know that all matter vibrates at different speeds.

978
01:25:41,800 --> 01:25:45,320
但在灵魂世界中 振动频率要高得多
But in the spirit world, operates at far higher levels.

979
01:25:45,480 --> 01:25:48,080
所以我们听不见他们说话 起码我们肉耳听不见
So we can't hear them. Not with our normal hearing.

980
01:25:48,280 --> 01:25:51,320
因此 我们所需要的是个全方位的…
So, what we really need is an omnidirectional...

981
01:25:51,520 --> 01:25:54,280
…超心型指向电容器麦克风
...supercardioid condenser microphone.

982
01:25:54,720 --> 01:25:56,320
就像这个珍宝一样
Like this beauty.

983
01:25:56,640 --> 01:26:00,360
好了 我想我们准备好了
Right. I think we are ready.

984
01:26:03,160 --> 01:26:04,680
然后…
And....

985
01:26:09,040 --> 01:26:12,400
杰森？你在吗？
Jason? Are you there?

986
01:26:14,000 --> 01:26:19,200
你的兄弟 马克斯 在这里 有什么想对他说的吗？
Your brother, Marcus, is here. Is there a message for him?

987
01:26:21,920 --> 01:26:25,200
最早是古希腊人发现这个的
It was the ancient Greeks who first discovered it.

988
01:26:26,480 --> 01:26:28,880
他们称之为"幻镜"
"psychomanteum," they called it.

989
01:26:29,040 --> 01:26:32,520
能反光的表面便是阴阳门
The reflective surface being the conduit to the afterlife.

990
01:26:32,720 --> 01:26:35,600
如今 我们称之为"镜面注视法"
Nowadays, we call it "mirror gazing."

991
01:26:35,760 --> 01:26:39,120
或许你没法跟他讲话 但你能看到他…
You might not be able to speak to him, but you will see him...

992
01:26:39,280 --> 01:26:41,480
…如果你真的想的话 就这样
...if you really want to, that is.

993
01:26:43,400 --> 01:26:44,880
你看到他了吗？
Did you see him?

994
01:26:45,040 --> 01:26:46,400
没有
No.

995
01:26:51,000 --> 01:26:52,880
你好 我是克莱尔
Hello. Clare speaking.

996
01:26:53,080 --> 01:26:55,360
完全没他的消息 我要报警了
There's no sign of him. I'm gonna call the police.

997
01:26:55,520 --> 01:26:58,400
- 但那样也没用的啊  - 好吧 我不在乎…
- But that will not help. - Well, I don't care what...

998
01:26:59,040 --> 01:27:02,200
等等 他就在这 我回头打给你
Hang on. He's here. I'll call you right back.

999
01:27:05,400 --> 01:27:07,040
我很抱歉
I'm sorry.

1000
01:27:07,200 --> 01:27:08,520
啊…
Ah...

1001
01:27:09,280 --> 01:27:10,920
由他去吧
Leave him be.

1002
01:28:19,440 --> 01:28:20,480
小心！
Watch out!

1003
01:28:29,640 --> 01:28:31,040
抱歉 让一下
Excuse me.

1004
01:29:48,280 --> 01:29:50,120
对不起 我们有点晚了
Sorry, we are running a little late.

1005
01:29:50,280 --> 01:29:51,320
请进
Come in.

1006
01:29:51,520 --> 01:29:54,400
大家被这些突发事件搅得心烦意乱
Everyone is upset by the events.

1007
01:29:58,840 --> 01:30:00,040
请坐
Sit down.

1008
01:30:03,240 --> 01:30:06,000
玛丽 实话告诉你 我有些疑惑
Marie, to be honest with you, I'm a bit confused.

1009
01:30:07,040 --> 01:30:09,080
我记得我们委托你写的是《密特朗总统传》
I thought we commissioned a book about Francois Mitterrand.

1010
01:30:09,240 --> 01:30:11,840
而你给我的前三章内容是…
Instead, you give us the first three chapters of...

1011
01:30:12,040 --> 01:30:13,080
…“未来:
...Hereafter:

1012
01:30:14,680 --> 01:30:16,440
沉默的阴谋”
The Conspiracy of Silence.

1013
01:30:16,600 --> 01:30:20,160
我知道这不是你们所期待的
I realize it's not what you were expecting.

1014
01:30:20,760 --> 01:30:23,720
你总是说出版业缺少惊喜
You always said there weren't enough surprises in publishing.

1015
01:30:23,880 --> 01:30:26,000
是吗 这的确是个惊喜！
Well, this is certainly a surprise!

1016
01:30:31,640 --> 01:30:33,840
我不知道从何说起
I don't know where to begin.

1017
01:30:34,000 --> 01:30:35,520
你难道不觉得我写的东西很有趣吗？
Did you at least find it interesting?

1018
01:30:35,680 --> 01:30:39,480
当然有趣 你总是善于发掘好的故事
Of course. You've always had a nose for a good story.

1019
01:30:39,640 --> 01:30:41,440
但我们是一个政府出版社…
But we're a political publisher...

1020
01:30:41,640 --> 01:30:42,840
这是和政治有关的！
This is political!

1021
01:30:43,040 --> 01:30:47,240
这种素材 再怎么吸引人也都是针对特殊市场
This kind of material, however fascinating, is for a specialized market.

1022
01:30:47,400 --> 01:30:50,440
今天早晨 在伦敦 6枚炸弹于市中心爆炸
This morning, in London, six bombs went off in the heart of the city.

1023
01:30:50,640 --> 01:30:55,040
显然有组织策划 炸弹是在交通高峰时段爆炸的
Apparently coordinated, the bombs exploded at the height of the rush hour.

1024
01:30:59,280 --> 01:31:01,080
为什么你们都反对我写的东西？
Why are you all against this?

1025
01:31:08,360 --> 01:31:10,640
为什么你们这么害怕？
Why are you so afraid of this?

1026
01:31:11,200 --> 01:31:12,560
这才是事实！
This is real!

1027
01:31:13,920 --> 01:31:15,760
这些科学证据…
This is scientific evidence...

1028
01:31:15,920 --> 01:31:18,920
…是知名科学家被迫秘密研究得来的
...from well-known researchers forced to work in secret.

1029
01:31:20,000 --> 01:31:24,080
一个诺贝尔奖得主 一直被宗教团体所困扰 这是真事
A Nobel prize winner, hounded by the religious lobby. That's a story!

1030
01:31:25,200 --> 01:31:28,360
比写一个调戏女人 不老实的老政客强得多
Better than a philandering, dishonest old politician.

1031
01:31:28,520 --> 01:31:32,320
但这样的书应该用英文写…
But a book like that would probably have to be written in English...

1032
01:31:32,520 --> 01:31:34,240
…针对美国市场
...for the American market.

1033
01:31:35,360 --> 01:31:37,160
我亲身经历过 米歇尔
It happened to me, Michel.

1034
01:31:39,040 --> 01:31:40,920
我亲眼所见
I saw it with my own eyes.

1035
01:31:42,240 --> 01:31:43,760
我们会魂归何处
Where we're going.

1036
01:31:45,720 --> 01:31:47,440
以及我们会经历的事情
What we'll experience.

1037
01:31:49,120 --> 01:31:51,200
我们中的每个人
Each and every one of us.

1038
01:31:53,480 --> 01:31:55,120
这难道不吸引你吗？
That doesn't interest you?

1039
01:31:59,360 --> 01:32:02,880
听者，我们委托你写的是《密特朗总统传》
Now listen, we commissioned a book about Francois Mitterrand.

1040
01:32:03,400 --> 01:32:05,920
要么达成协议 你开始写我们要求的…
Either we agree on this and you start writing it...

1041
01:32:06,120 --> 01:32:08,920
…要么我就把钱要回来 我就说这么多
...or else I want my money back. That's all I can say.

1042
01:32:32,720 --> 01:32:34,360
真是丢人
It was so humiliating.

1043
01:32:36,000 --> 01:32:38,640
他们看我的眼神就好像我是个疯子
They looked at me as if I'd lost my mind.

1044
01:32:38,800 --> 01:32:41,600
6个月前他们祈求我随便写点什么
Six months ago they begged me to write about anything.

1045
01:32:42,480 --> 01:32:44,920
伟大的玛丽·勒莱写的任何东西都行
Anything by the great Marie Lelay.

1046
01:32:46,680 --> 01:32:50,320
你最好把我的工作还我 我受够这种羞辱了
You'd better give me my job back. I've had enough with being humiliated.

1047
01:32:54,040 --> 01:32:56,000
今天 他们甚至把我的海报都换下来了
Today, they even took down my posters.

1048
01:32:59,520 --> 01:33:00,840
为什么你没和我说这事？
Why didn't you tell me?

1049
01:33:03,120 --> 01:33:04,400
你的书进展如何？
And your book?

1050
01:33:06,400 --> 01:33:10,000
我会在空闲时间写完它 它已经让我够麻烦的了
I'll finish it in my spare time. It's caused me enough trouble as it is.

1051
01:33:13,360 --> 01:33:14,520
到底怎么回事？
What's the matter?

1052
01:33:15,680 --> 01:33:16,920
听着…
Look...

1053
01:33:17,560 --> 01:33:19,800
…要找回你的工作…
...getting your job back...

1054
01:33:20,000 --> 01:33:22,160
…可能没你想象的那么容易
...might not be as easy as you think.

1055
01:33:23,120 --> 01:33:24,160
为什么？
Why?

1056
01:33:24,840 --> 01:33:27,160
我只是申请了短假 而且是你建议的
It was a temporary break. And on your advice.

1057
01:33:27,920 --> 01:33:29,000
我知道 但是…
I know, but...

1058
01:33:30,040 --> 01:33:31,720
我们当时没想到…
What we couldn't have foreseen is...

1059
01:33:31,880 --> 01:33:34,880
…你会公开谈论你的体验
...you'd be talking in public about these experiences.

1060
01:33:35,040 --> 01:33:39,280
- 你失去了你的信誉   - 但我不想写这本书！
- That you'd lose your credibility. - But I didn't want to write this book!

1061
01:33:39,480 --> 01:33:41,040
那是你的主意！
It was your idea!

1062
01:33:41,200 --> 01:33:43,680
我的主意是让你写密特朗总统
It was my idea you should write about Mitterrand.

1063
01:33:44,720 --> 01:33:46,520
那么 你到底要说什么？
So, what are you saying?

1064
01:33:47,840 --> 01:33:50,360
我是说你再花点时间
I'm saying take some more time.

1065
01:33:50,560 --> 01:33:53,560
完成这本书 等它出版后你解放了 再回来
Finish the book, get it out of your system, then come back.

1066
01:33:54,600 --> 01:33:56,880
是那个女孩 对吧？替代我的女孩？
It's that girl, isn't it? My replacement?

1067
01:33:58,600 --> 01:34:00,520
我见过她几次 她很漂亮
I've watched her a few times. She's good.

1068
01:34:01,000 --> 01:34:03,520
对 她是很棒 但没你出色
Yes, she is. But not as good as you.

1069
01:34:05,240 --> 01:34:06,760
你和她睡过了？
You're sleeping with her?

1070
01:34:08,200 --> 01:34:09,960
你怎么能这么说？
How can you say such a thing?

1071
01:34:12,720 --> 01:34:15,240
你总是告诉我要问一些尖锐的问题
You always told me to ask the tough questions.

1072
01:34:32,800 --> 01:34:34,120
真有趣…
It's funny....

1073
01:34:35,760 --> 01:34:37,400
谁能想到会变成这样？
Who'd have thought it?

1074
01:34:39,880 --> 01:34:41,720
几个月前我很出名
A few months ago I was famous.

1075
01:34:42,600 --> 01:34:44,080
也很富有
Rich.

1076
01:34:45,640 --> 01:34:47,120
是个成功人士
A success story.

1077
01:34:49,440 --> 01:34:50,920
那时我很快乐
I was happy.

1078
01:34:52,560 --> 01:34:54,720
生活被工作填满
Fulfilled by my work.

1079
01:34:56,240 --> 01:34:57,720
还有你
By you.

1080
01:35:12,760 --> 01:35:16,240
一切的开始是因为你没有给你的孩子们买礼物
All this happened because you didn't buy your kids their gifts.

1081
01:35:16,440 --> 01:35:17,880
因为什么？
Because of what?

1082
01:35:18,040 --> 01:35:20,640
你在说什么？我不明白
What are you talking about? I don't understand.

1083
01:35:22,320 --> 01:35:23,920
忘了吧 那无关紧要
Forget it. It doesn't matter.

1084
01:35:49,280 --> 01:35:50,280
我是米歇尔
It's Michel.

1085
01:35:51,960 --> 01:35:53,120
听着…
Listen....

1086
01:35:54,640 --> 01:35:57,360
我对今早我们的谈话感觉很抱歉
I feel terrible about our meeting earlier today.

1087
01:35:59,000 --> 01:36:01,720
这本书显然对你很重要
This book is obviously very important to you.

1088
01:36:03,360 --> 01:36:06,880
我想今早大家对在伦敦发生的事故 有些紧张烦躁
I think everyone was a bit on edge because of the events in London.

1089
01:36:09,120 --> 01:36:13,960
但之后我打了几个电话 有两个出版商对你的书感兴趣
But I made a few calls. There are two publishers who might be interested.

1090
01:36:14,640 --> 01:36:16,600
一个在美国 一个在英国
One American, one English.

1091
01:36:17,640 --> 01:36:18,800
你有笔吗？
Do you have a pen?

1092
01:36:26,600 --> 01:36:28,040
我听着呢
I'm listening.

1093
01:36:50,000 --> 01:36:53,240
不管怎样 我觉得这会是一间理想的团体通灵室
Anyways, I thought this would be a good group reading room.

1094
01:36:53,400 --> 01:36:54,400
团体通灵？
Group reading?

1095
01:36:54,600 --> 01:36:57,080
对 在这里你一次可以通灵更多人
Yeah, where you could read more people at once.

1096
01:36:57,240 --> 01:37:00,600
多到20个甚至更多 你做主 不过这样他们付的钱就少了
Up to 20 people or more, it's up to you. They'd pay lower rates that way.

1097
01:37:00,760 --> 01:37:02,840
这间会是你的私人咨询室
This would be your personal consulting room.

1098
01:37:03,000 --> 01:37:07,280
就在这间隔壁 乔治 这会是我的房间
And right next door, George, this is gonna be my room.

1099
01:37:07,440 --> 01:37:09,880
我会把每件事打理得井井有条
I'm gonna make sure everything gets taken care of.

1100
01:37:10,040 --> 01:37:11,520
你就不必操心了
You won't have to worry.

1101
01:37:12,040 --> 01:37:14,520
我不明白 那你的其它工作怎么办？
I don't understand. What about your other businesses?

1102
01:37:14,720 --> 01:37:16,440
哦 对 当然 那些都是神马浮云
Oh, yeah, of course. They're gone.

1103
01:37:16,600 --> 01:37:18,760
等这边一运转起来 忘了它们 明白吗？
Once this thing takes off, forget it, you know?

1104
01:37:18,920 --> 01:37:21,800
我送你回家吧 你需要休息 明天对你来说很重要
Let's get you home. You need rest. You got a big day tomorrow.

1105
01:37:21,960 --> 01:37:23,840
你已经有三个预约了
You already have three appointments.

1106
01:37:24,040 --> 01:37:25,360
- 行吗？  - 好吧
- All right? - Yeah.

1107
01:37:25,520 --> 01:37:26,880
走吧
Come on.

1108
01:37:53,280 --> 01:37:55,640
- 你是比利·洛里根？- 没错
- You Billy Lonegan? - Yes.

1109
01:37:55,800 --> 01:37:57,920
你兄弟在走之前 让我把这个给你
Before he went, your brother asked me to give this to you.

1110
01:37:58,080 --> 01:37:59,600
走？走哪里去了？
Went? Went where?

1111
01:37:59,760 --> 01:38:01,240
我也不知道
I have no idea.

1112
01:38:07,720 --> 01:38:09,000
亲爱的比利…
Dear Billy...

1113
01:38:09,480 --> 01:38:10,760
…我很抱歉
...I'm sorry.

1114
01:38:10,920 --> 01:38:14,040
我猜无论我说什么 都无法让你信服…
I guess there's nothing I'll ever be able to say to persuade you...

1115
01:38:14,200 --> 01:38:16,720
…我所拥有的不是天赋 而是一个诅咒
...that what I have isn't a gift, but a curse.

1116
01:38:17,440 --> 01:38:20,640
我知道你认为我天生注定要去帮助别人
I know you feel what I have comes with a duty to help others

1117
01:38:20,800 --> 01:38:24,240
但现在 我最需要帮助的人是我自己
But right now, the person I most need to help is myself.

1118
01:38:24,400 --> 01:38:26,840
所以我决定出去走走
So I've decided to take some time out.

1119
01:38:27,040 --> 01:38:29,960
我不清楚未来会发生什么 也不知道何时会回来
I don't know what the future will bring or when I'll be back.

1120
01:38:30,120 --> 01:38:32,600
所以别等我 可以这么说
So don't wait up, so to speak.

1121
01:38:32,800 --> 01:38:36,640
向珍妮和孩子们问好 你的小兄弟乔治敬上
Love to Jenni and the kids Your baby brother, George.

1122
01:38:51,160 --> 01:38:54,120
你应该知道这种精神伤害病例的恢复率
You know the recovery rate in substance abuse cases like this.

1123
01:38:54,680 --> 01:38:56,880
- 是的  - 知道 非常低
- Yeah. - Yeah. Very low.

1124
01:38:57,840 --> 01:39:01,200
那么 以后最好的方法是什么？你可以再等段时间吗？
So, what's the best way forward? Are you okay for a little bit longer?

1125
01:39:02,800 --> 01:39:06,240
是的 但别太久 拜托
Yes. But not too long, please.

1126
01:39:06,440 --> 01:39:09,880
我们快没辙了 那已经开始造成伤害了
We're running out of ideas, and it's beginning to take its toll.

1127
01:39:10,400 --> 01:39:12,720
带他去见见我们很早以前帮助过的孩子 瑞奇
Taking him to see our previous child, Ricky.

1128
01:39:14,760 --> 01:39:17,560
谁能明白 你能明白吗？一个孩子在和另一个说话
Who knows, you know? One kid talking to another.

1129
01:39:30,360 --> 01:39:32,120
- 玛丽·勒菜？- 什么事？
- Marie Lelay? - Yes?

1130
01:39:32,280 --> 01:39:36,480
我是理查德·亚纶森 新墨西哥州圣达菲的宝瓶出版社的
This is Richard Aronson of Aquarius Books in Santa Fe, New Mexico.

1131
01:39:36,640 --> 01:39:37,960
抱歉您说什么？
Excuse me?

1132
01:39:38,120 --> 01:39:41,800
您忘了圣达菲的宝瓶出版社？几个月前你给我们寄过你的书
Aquarius books in Santa Fe? A few months ago, you sent us your book.

1133
01:39:42,000 --> 01:39:44,080
我打电话是想告诉你 我们很喜欢你的书
I'm just ringing to say how much we liked it.

1134
01:39:44,240 --> 01:39:47,600
抱歉 过了这么久 但我们确实很喜欢它并且决定出版你的书
Sorry it's taken so long, but we loved it, and we'd like to publish it.

1135
01:39:47,760 --> 01:39:49,880
- 真的吗？- 事实上 我们想在…
- Really? - In fact, we'd like to print it...

1136
01:39:50,080 --> 01:39:53,040
…明年春季伦敦书展的时候印刷出版
...in time for a book fair in London in the spring.

1137
01:39:53,200 --> 01:39:55,320
- 你住在巴黎吗？- 是的
- You're based in Paris? - Yes

1138
01:39:55,520 --> 01:39:58,840
那么 如果我们邀请您去伦敦会不会给您造成不便？
So, if we were to ask going to London wouldn't be inconvenient?

1139
01:39:59,000 --> 01:40:00,960
不会 不 不 不 完全不会
No. No, no, no, not at all.

1140
01:40:01,160 --> 01:40:03,640
做一些宣传是很好的机会
That would be a good opportunity to do some publicity.

1141
01:40:03,800 --> 01:40:06,800
可能会办个朗诵会 那真是个不可思议的故事
Maybe a reading. It's an incredible story.

1142
01:40:06,960 --> 01:40:08,720
谢谢
Thank you.

1143
01:40:14,520 --> 01:40:16,280
我们到了
And here we are.

1144
01:40:18,240 --> 01:40:20,720
道提街48号
48 Doughty Street.

1145
01:40:20,920 --> 01:40:22,640
查尔斯·狄更斯在伦敦的家…
Charles Dickens' home in London...

1146
01:40:22,840 --> 01:40:26,680
…他和妻子凯瑟琳以及他们的孩子们住在这里
...where he lived with his wife Catherine and their children.

1147
01:40:26,880 --> 01:40:29,480
谁知道他们有多少个孩子吗？
Anyone know how many children?

1148
01:40:31,200 --> 01:40:33,360
我们现在在主门厅
Here we are in the main hallway.

1149
01:40:33,560 --> 01:40:36,000
- 这是作家每次进门时…  - 10个孩子
- This is the view that greeted the author... - Ten.

1150
01:40:36,160 --> 01:40:37,880
…欢迎他回家的图画
...as he walked in each time.

1151
01:40:38,040 --> 01:40:40,840
每件东西都是原样重现
Everything has been preserved exactly as it was.

1152
01:40:41,000 --> 01:40:45,200
请跟我上楼 我们从顶层介绍起
So just follow me up the stairs. We'll start at the top of the house.

1153
01:40:48,600 --> 01:40:51,080
我们现在走进的是狄更斯的书房
Now we move in to Dickens' study.

1154
01:40:51,240 --> 01:40:55,160
在你们面前 你们看到的是《圣诞颂歌》的原稿…
And directly in front of you, you'll see an original copy of A Christmas Carol...

1155
01:40:55,320 --> 01:40:58,520
…狄更斯具有争议的最著名的小说之一
...arguably one of Dickens' most famous books.

1156
01:40:59,040 --> 01:41:02,160
这里 有样东西我觉得你们都值得一看
But over here, the thing I expect most of you have come to see.

1157
01:41:02,320 --> 01:41:04,520
狄更斯的书桌 在这里他完成了他的大部分著作
Dickens' desk, where he wrote most of his books.

1158
01:41:05,320 --> 01:41:09,920
墙上有几幅《德鲁德疑案》里的插图…
On this wall we have several illustrations for The Mystery of Edwin Drood...

1159
01:41:10,080 --> 01:41:13,120
…那是狄更斯在生命所剩无几的时候写的小说
...the novel Dickens was writing at the time of his death.

1160
01:41:13,920 --> 01:41:17,800
这边的墙上 这幅画是狄更斯小说迷们的最爱
And on the far wall here, a painting loved by Dickens fans.

1161
01:41:18,000 --> 01:41:20,400
画的是作家在书桌上睡着了…
It shows the author asleep at his desk...

1162
01:41:20,600 --> 01:41:23,680
…他小说中的人物在他周围漂浮着
...with characters from his novels floating in the air around him.

1163
01:41:25,040 --> 01:41:27,320
谁知道这幅画的名字？
Anyone know its name?

1164
01:41:27,480 --> 01:41:29,200
《狄更斯的梦》
Dickens' Dream.

1165
01:41:29,360 --> 01:41:32,520
它被命名为《狄更斯的梦》
It's called Dickens' Dream.

1166
01:41:35,880 --> 01:41:37,120
这边 请跟我来
This way, please.

1167
01:41:39,440 --> 01:41:42,880
请在楼前集合
Just gather again at the front of the building.

1168
01:41:49,080 --> 01:41:51,040
谁有什么问题吗？
Does anyone have any questions?

1169
01:41:56,520 --> 01:41:58,320
今天几号了？
What is the date today?

1170
01:41:58,520 --> 01:42:01,840
- 14号  - 是14号 好的 谢谢
- Fourteenth. - It is the 14th. Yeah, okay.

1171
01:42:05,280 --> 01:42:07,280
我想你会喜欢瑞奇的
I think you'll like Ricky.

1172
01:42:07,480 --> 01:42:11,160
我们第一次见他时 他和你差不多大小哦 也和你一样害羞
He was about your age when he first came to us, and just as shy.

1173
01:42:11,720 --> 01:42:16,080
现在他长成个大人了 有工作还有自己的公寓
Now he's a grown man. With a job and his own flat.

1174
01:42:20,400 --> 01:42:23,160
- 他就在这里的某个地方 - 他说在大厅和我们碰面
- He's in here somewhere. - He said he'd meet us at the front.

1175
01:42:23,360 --> 01:42:25,200
他在哪里？
Where is he?

1176
01:42:25,360 --> 01:42:28,200
- 他在哪里？- 嘿 瞧瞧
- Where is he? - Hey. Look at this.

1177
01:42:28,360 --> 01:42:30,080
- 嗨   - 哈 哈 哈
- Hey. - Heh, heh, heh.

1178
01:42:33,080 --> 01:42:35,480
哦 老天 我都认不出你了
